From: Andrew Morton <akpm@linux-foundation.org>
Date: Fri, 27 Mar 2026 12:28:40 -0700
Subject: [PATCH] selftests-mm-vm_util-robust-write_file-fix

add newline, per David

Cc: David Hildenbrand (Arm) <david@kernel.org>
Cc: Chunyu Hu <chuhu@redhat.com>
Signed-off-by: Andrew Morton <akpm@linux-foundation.org>
---
 tools/testing/selftests/mm/vm_util.c | 1 +
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+)

diff --git a/tools/testing/selftests/mm/vm_util.c b/tools/testing/selftests/mm/vm_util.c
index 572ccb99de8e..33e78a5abfeb 100644
--- a/tools/testing/selftests/mm/vm_util.c
+++ b/tools/testing/selftests/mm/vm_util.c
@@ -769,6 +769,7 @@ void write_file(const char *path, const char *buf, size_t buflen)
 {
 	int fd, saved_errno;
 	ssize_t numwritten;
+
 	if (buflen < 1)
 		ksft_exit_fail_msg("Incorrect buffer len: %zu\n", buflen);
 
